I"È<h3 id="diet-a-diet-that-stabilises-your-blood-sugar">Diet a diet that stabilises your blood sugar</h3>
<p>If your blood sugar is low, it triggers the stress response which makes you more likely to feel anxiety.</p>

<h3 id="speaking-about-it">Speaking about it</h3>
<p>Research shows that when we form connections with other people, we are reducing cortisol in the body. Our parasympathetic nervous system is turned off when we feel safe and supported.</p>

<h3 id="sleep---at-least-8-hours">Sleep - at least 8 hours</h3>
<p>Sleep is designed to reduce stress levels as it allows you to release the resistance that causes anxiety. Your fight or fight response is triggered when you do not get enough sleep.</p>
